[step 3] MTP draft acceptance context sweep
  - two prompt modes tested: repeat (biased) and truncate (more realistic)
  - repeat mode (first run, caveat): 95% acceptance plateau at >1K tokens
    because the model echoes the repeated prompt back
  - truncate mode (re-run with long natural prose): 62-94% range, high
    variance depending on paragraph boundaries in the truncation point
  - headline: generation t/s is FLAT from 184 tokens up to 4440 tokens
    (36.9-38.0 t/s, <3% delta over 24x context increase)
  - MTP acceptance rate depends on prompt character, not context length:
    instructive/directive prompts ~65-70%, natural-prose continuation ~90%+
  - step 1 baseline at 69.9% is realistic for agent workloads, not pessimistic
  - status: OK
